WEBVTT

00:01.436 --> 00:02.741
Previously onSWAT...

00:02.785 --> 00:04.091
Hondo's a good guy,
but everyone knows

00:04.134 --> 00:06.571
that his promotion
was affirmative action nonsense.

00:06.615 --> 00:07.790
Why were you
recording them?

00:07.833 --> 00:09.270
They're racists, Annie.

00:09.313 --> 00:10.401
So what are we gonna do
about it?

00:10.445 --> 00:11.402
I'm not going to IA with just

00:11.446 --> 00:12.577
my word against theirs.

00:12.621 --> 00:13.578
The Board of Rights

00:13.622 --> 00:14.666
reached a decision regarding

00:14.710 --> 00:15.798
Lee Durham's punishment.

00:15.841 --> 00:17.974
He will not be fired
from the LAPD.

00:18.018 --> 00:19.802
Maybe we got one last card
we can play.

00:19.845 --> 00:21.151
You're talking
about going to the press?

00:21.195 --> 00:22.413
Do you see any other option?

00:22.457 --> 00:24.111
What you are talking about

00:24.154 --> 00:25.808
is career suicide.

00:25.851 --> 00:27.636
There's gonna be an article
in the L.A. Times

00:27.679 --> 00:30.073
coming out tomorrow. They'll be
printing my name as the source.

00:30.117 --> 00:31.640
Mayor's gonna
have your head for this.

00:31.683 --> 00:33.642
I know.I met with the chief.

00:33.685 --> 00:36.079
You're being demoted
from 20-Squad leader.

00:36.123 --> 00:39.996
They want to force me to quit so
they can keep their hands clean.

00:40.040 --> 00:42.651
I ain't gonna lie.
I did not see that one coming.

00:42.694 --> 00:45.480
If you want to take some time
to decide what you want to do,

00:45.523 --> 00:49.005
just know two things.
One-- I'm on your side,

00:49.049 --> 00:52.313
and two-- you helped
save this city.

01:00.364 --> 01:02.410
♪

01:29.350 --> 01:31.787
♪

02:01.556 --> 02:03.558
♪

02:32.804 --> 02:34.937
♪

03:05.794 --> 03:07.012
Willie...

03:25.683 --> 03:29.034
How many times do we got
to go through this, Willie?

03:29.078 --> 03:32.212
I'm tired.
Aren't you tired?

03:38.870 --> 03:40.829
Stubborn,

03:40.872 --> 03:43.571
old anddumb?

03:45.877 --> 03:47.314
Damn.

03:50.534 --> 03:52.536
No, no. No, no.Hey!

04:07.595 --> 04:09.074
Get your car off my property.

04:09.118 --> 04:12.208
You know,
I've never seen you smile.

04:13.340 --> 04:15.211
Why so mad all the time?

04:15.255 --> 04:17.213
Especially when me
and my father are offering you

04:17.257 --> 04:19.259
a very, very, very fair deal.

04:21.826 --> 04:24.089
Take your money
and shove it right...

04:25.134 --> 04:26.222
Hey.
[speaks Spanish]

04:26.266 --> 04:28.224
HONDO:
Is there a problem here?

04:31.662 --> 04:33.098
Are you lost?

04:33.142 --> 04:34.448
No.

04:39.017 --> 04:41.368
But I think you're on
my friend's property.

04:41.411 --> 04:42.978
I've been staying
at his place.

04:43.021 --> 04:44.632
This is not your friend's land.

04:44.675 --> 04:46.460
Is that right?

04:46.503 --> 04:48.418
It's mine.
And my mother's.

04:48.462 --> 04:49.767
Well, I guess it's hard
to know when one ranch ends

04:49.811 --> 04:51.378
and another begins
with no fences.

04:51.421 --> 04:53.728
Now that you know, get lost.

05:00.952 --> 05:02.345
So this is your place?

05:02.389 --> 05:03.390
Yes.

05:04.434 --> 05:06.610
It's very beautiful.

05:06.654 --> 05:08.395
And these two guys--

05:08.438 --> 05:09.961
they're guests of yours?

05:10.962 --> 05:12.442
Trespassers.

05:13.487 --> 05:18.230
Señor, my friend
asked you to leave.

05:18.274 --> 05:19.319
You should
listen to him.

05:30.025 --> 05:32.419
His nose doesn't
look broken,

05:32.462 --> 05:33.942
but you might want
to take him to get some ice.

05:54.354 --> 05:56.181
I'll see you soon, Delfina.

06:00.360 --> 06:02.884
My mother rejected every one
of your father's offers.

06:04.451 --> 06:07.584
You and he can both go to hell.

06:12.067 --> 06:13.851
American?

06:15.287 --> 06:16.332
Who are you?

06:16.376 --> 06:18.334
Nobody.

06:18.378 --> 06:20.771
I just came across people
needing help.

06:22.860 --> 06:24.253
Amigo?

06:24.296 --> 06:26.298
Gracias.

06:41.488 --> 06:44.229
You don't ever
run into me again.

06:45.753 --> 06:47.450
Understand?

06:52.629 --> 06:54.065
All right.

07:03.335 --> 07:05.337
♪

07:12.214 --> 07:13.694
Morning, Señor Harrelson.

07:13.737 --> 07:14.869
HONDO:
Buenos días, señora.

07:14.912 --> 07:17.349
Uh... ¿Cómo estás hoy?

07:17.393 --> 07:19.395
Yeah?Not bad.

07:19.439 --> 07:21.005
If you like the sound

07:21.049 --> 07:22.746
of nails on a chalkboard.Well, my Spanish

07:22.790 --> 07:25.009
is just about as good
as your cooking, okay?

07:25.053 --> 07:27.534
Don Anthony did not hire me

07:27.577 --> 07:29.579
to boil beans
and press tortillas all day.

07:29.623 --> 07:31.276
Well, you do run a tight ship
around here, Paloma.

07:31.320 --> 07:32.930
No doubt about it.

07:32.974 --> 07:35.716
I heard you were quite the hero
this morning.

07:37.761 --> 07:39.459
It was nothing.

07:39.502 --> 07:41.461
Not according to Delfina Reyes.

07:41.504 --> 07:43.288
I don't know who that is.

07:43.332 --> 07:45.987
She and her mother own
that big farm across the creek.

07:47.597 --> 07:49.817
You met that Novak son,
the gringo?

07:49.860 --> 07:52.254
His name's A.J.
Es un maldito.

07:52.297 --> 07:55.431
Bad. And those poor women...

07:55.475 --> 07:56.998
They've been through
enough tragedy.

07:57.041 --> 07:59.087
How's that?
Their father,
Don Miguel--

07:59.130 --> 08:00.523
he died a few months ago.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.482
Accident working the fields.

08:02.525 --> 08:04.353
So sad.

08:05.397 --> 08:07.312
The Reyes have had
that farm forever.

08:07.356 --> 08:08.749
They're good people.

08:11.752 --> 08:13.884
All I did was change a tire.

08:36.907 --> 08:38.909
[vehicle approaching]

08:49.485 --> 08:51.182
Can I help you, Officer?

08:51.226 --> 08:53.184
I'm looking into a
confrontation that happened

08:53.228 --> 08:54.534
earlier today at
the Reyes farm.

08:54.577 --> 08:56.057
Were you there?

08:57.145 --> 09:00.365
I was there...
afterthe confrontation.

09:00.409 --> 09:02.280
What's your name?Harrelson.

09:02.324 --> 09:04.587
You need to take my statement?

09:04.631 --> 09:06.328
No. That won't
be necessary.

09:06.371 --> 09:09.244
My boss, the chief, asked me
to come by and see the man

09:09.287 --> 09:11.072
who's been causing
problems with our locals.

09:11.115 --> 09:13.553
[scoffs] I'm afraid
you have the story wrong.

09:13.596 --> 09:15.859
I take it the Novak kid
left out the part

09:15.903 --> 09:17.252
where he assaulted an old man.

09:17.295 --> 09:20.081
Assault is
a very serious charge.

09:20.124 --> 09:21.517
How long you been
staying here?

09:21.561 --> 09:22.779
Couple of months.

09:22.823 --> 09:23.780
How long you plan on staying?

09:23.824 --> 09:25.303
Haven't decided yet.

09:25.347 --> 09:26.609
House belongs
to my friend Anthony.

09:26.653 --> 09:28.132
He says I can stay
as long as I'd like.

09:29.699 --> 09:32.615
Look, I know
you were probably just trying

09:32.659 --> 09:34.748
to help Delfina Reyes
and her farmworkers.

09:34.791 --> 09:36.401
To me, that's
a decent man.

09:36.445 --> 09:38.621
But I recommend
you stay away from A.J. Novak.

09:38.665 --> 09:40.405
You mess with him,
you mess with his father.

09:40.449 --> 09:42.407
You don't want
to mess with his father.

09:42.451 --> 09:44.366
We don't need any heroes
around here, you understand?

09:44.409 --> 09:47.499
I came here to get away from
problems, not find new ones.

09:47.543 --> 09:50.372
Then you understand. Bueno.

09:51.416 --> 09:53.462
Enjoy your stay,
Mr. Harrelson.

09:53.505 --> 09:55.507
Adios.

10:00.121 --> 10:02.036
That about what happened
at Los Reyes farm?

10:02.079 --> 10:03.341
[engine starts]

10:03.385 --> 10:05.996
Nothing happened.
It's over now.

10:07.345 --> 10:11.132
Well, Delfina--
it's not over for her.

10:11.175 --> 10:12.350
She called again.

10:12.394 --> 10:14.004
Her mother wants you
over for lunch today.

10:14.048 --> 10:16.572
You tell 'em I said,
"No thanks."

10:16.616 --> 10:18.835
Here, an invitation

10:18.879 --> 10:22.447
to break bread
is a high compliment.

10:22.491 --> 10:24.711
Do you want to piss off
your friend's neighbors?

10:29.716 --> 10:31.674
♪

10:45.601 --> 10:48.082
[door closes]

10:48.125 --> 10:49.474
You can use a hand.

10:49.518 --> 10:53.000
I am Isabel Reyes,
Delfina's mother.

10:53.043 --> 10:55.132
Daniel.

10:55.176 --> 10:58.527
Forgive me. We are down on
workers, so I had to help here

10:58.570 --> 11:01.008
so I lost track of time.It's quite all right.

11:01.051 --> 11:03.184
I can pitch in.No, no. Absolutely not.

11:03.227 --> 11:05.186
You're our guest for lunch.

11:05.229 --> 11:07.405
I really don't mind
working for my grub.

11:07.449 --> 11:09.538
Thank you.
Mm-hmm.

11:32.735 --> 11:35.129
Well, that's the, uh, hardest
I've worked in a while.

11:35.172 --> 11:37.218
Feels good.

11:37.261 --> 11:39.263
You must have a job
behind a desk.

11:40.612 --> 11:43.572
I don't want
to track dirt in your house.

11:43.615 --> 11:45.095
Wouldn't be
the first time.

11:45.139 --> 11:46.749
Well, it's my first time
in your home.

11:46.793 --> 11:49.578
You can use the wash
station over there.

11:49.621 --> 11:51.232
There are towels
under the sink,

11:51.275 --> 11:53.625
and I'll get a
clean shirt for you.

12:08.249 --> 12:10.251
[sniffs]

12:58.603 --> 13:01.519
His name is Arthur Novak. He's
some kind of European investor.

13:01.563 --> 13:02.956
We've never met him.

13:02.999 --> 13:04.784
His son A.J. handles
all negotiations.

13:04.827 --> 13:05.915
How long have he and his son...?

13:05.959 --> 13:07.743
And you saw the way A.J.
negotiates--

13:07.787 --> 13:09.658
like an animal, with threats
and knives. Ever since

13:09.701 --> 13:11.791
my father died, he's been
driving our farmworkers away,

13:11.834 --> 13:13.053
trying to force us to sell.

13:13.096 --> 13:14.489
How about
we let Daniel finish?

13:14.532 --> 13:16.143
All because why?

13:16.186 --> 13:17.753
We won't give him
and his father what they want?

13:17.797 --> 13:20.103
Delfina.

13:21.409 --> 13:23.150
Ms. Reyes, I have to say,
this is the best meal

13:23.193 --> 13:24.586
I've had here so far.

13:24.629 --> 13:25.848
Please, call me Isabel.

13:25.892 --> 13:27.981
And I am good,
but not that good.

13:28.024 --> 13:30.157
Top three, then.Hmm.

13:33.682 --> 13:35.771
I'm very sorry
to hear about your husband.

13:38.556 --> 13:40.515
My daughter takes after him.

13:40.558 --> 13:43.344
Very impatient,
but passionate.

13:43.387 --> 13:45.737
That's why
I fell in love with him.

13:47.217 --> 13:50.133
This land has been in our family
for six generations.

13:50.177 --> 13:52.875
Too long for us
to just sell it to someone.

13:55.530 --> 13:57.880
I'll get dessert.

14:03.581 --> 14:06.889
So, the worker who was injured--
he's all right?

14:06.933 --> 14:10.023
His nose wasn't broken,
like you said.

14:10.066 --> 14:12.025
How did you know that?

14:12.068 --> 14:13.374
Didn't look broke.

14:13.417 --> 14:14.766
Where in America are you from?

14:16.246 --> 14:18.335
Los Angeles.

14:18.379 --> 14:20.598
I was there once, as a kid.

14:20.642 --> 14:22.383
Too much noise.

14:22.426 --> 14:26.082
Hmm. Can't fight
you on that one.

14:26.126 --> 14:29.042
What do you do there? For work?

14:32.784 --> 14:35.526
I'm not sure.

14:35.570 --> 14:37.224
That's why I came here--

14:37.267 --> 14:39.748
to block out
all the noise and...

14:39.791 --> 14:42.838
figure out my next move.

14:45.319 --> 14:47.408
It's incredible.

14:47.451 --> 14:50.498
Seems to go on forever.120 acres.

14:50.541 --> 14:52.630
Most family farms here
are too small to succeed.

14:52.674 --> 14:55.155
We've been lucky.

14:55.198 --> 14:57.418
Six generations.
Got to be more than luck.

14:57.461 --> 15:00.073
[laughs]My family has
survived it all.

15:00.116 --> 15:05.121
Chaos, dictatorship,
bandits, the revolution.

15:05.165 --> 15:07.254
We've fought too hard
to sell to greedy bastards.

15:07.297 --> 15:09.125
They offer you a fair price?I suppose.

15:09.169 --> 15:10.910
But we never wanted the farm
to make us rich.

15:10.953 --> 15:12.781
Just to make our lives good.

15:12.824 --> 15:14.870
And now, with this Novak kid
scaring off your workers...

15:14.914 --> 15:16.219
I don't know how

15:16.263 --> 15:17.829
we take care of our crops.

15:19.440 --> 15:21.833
Who was the guy with Arthur's
son this morning? The local?

15:21.877 --> 15:24.575
Gabriel. He used to work for us.

15:24.619 --> 15:26.534
I got the feeling there was

15:26.577 --> 15:28.797
more than that
between you two.We dated.

15:28.840 --> 15:31.104
Ended bad?

15:31.147 --> 15:33.236
My father hoped
we'd get married one day,

15:33.280 --> 15:35.238
take over the farm together.

15:35.282 --> 15:37.153
And I would have.

15:37.197 --> 15:38.633
He betrayed you.

15:39.677 --> 15:41.679
Broke my heart.

15:43.029 --> 15:45.945
My mother's too proud to
admit it, but she's scared.

15:45.988 --> 15:47.598
This is our home,

15:47.642 --> 15:49.774
and now we're too afraid to even
go into town to buy supplies,

15:49.818 --> 15:52.255
in case we run into any of them.

15:52.299 --> 15:55.258
I was gonna take a drive
into town today.

15:56.346 --> 15:59.001
You can come with me,
get what you need.

15:59.045 --> 16:01.221
You would do that?

16:03.919 --> 16:05.268
[Spanish music playing]

16:05.312 --> 16:07.096
HONDO:
Wow. You aren't playing.

16:07.140 --> 16:09.838
Is this everything?[laughs]
One more stop maybe.

16:09.881 --> 16:11.274
My mother and
her spices.

16:11.318 --> 16:12.667
Only one shop will do.

16:12.710 --> 16:14.495
[gasps]Look.

16:14.538 --> 16:17.019
♪

16:17.063 --> 16:18.847
The best ice cream
you've ever had.

16:18.890 --> 16:21.328
All the American ice cream
combined cannot compare.

16:21.371 --> 16:22.938
Careful now.

16:22.982 --> 16:24.418
You get in line.

16:24.461 --> 16:26.028
I'll get
my mother's spices.

16:26.072 --> 16:27.334
I'll be back in time to order.

16:27.377 --> 16:29.379
Okay.

16:30.424 --> 16:32.730
I'll be right back.
Two minutes.

16:37.344 --> 16:38.998
Gracias.Mm-hmm.

16:44.525 --> 16:46.005
Delfina.

17:09.332 --> 17:11.334
You're crazy in the head.

17:11.378 --> 17:13.641
Do you not like money, Delfina?

17:13.684 --> 17:16.470
Something about money
that... bothers you?

17:16.513 --> 17:18.167
Just your money.

17:18.211 --> 17:21.736
Or should I say your
father's money, pendejo?

17:21.779 --> 17:24.086
The mouth on this one...

17:24.130 --> 17:25.783
A.J., stop. Please.

17:26.828 --> 17:28.264
Let me go now.

17:28.308 --> 17:30.092
Money doesn't know
where it came from.

17:30.136 --> 17:32.094
It's just money.

17:32.138 --> 17:33.922
We're offering you more
than enough of it,

17:33.965 --> 17:36.098
so stop pretending
you're too good to take it.

17:36.142 --> 17:38.753
Move, please. I have to go.

17:38.796 --> 17:40.450
What is that scent?

17:40.494 --> 17:42.017
Is that coconut?

17:42.061 --> 17:43.801
HONDO:
She said she has to go.

17:45.151 --> 17:46.500
Step aside.

17:46.543 --> 17:48.763
We're just having a
conversation, a private one.

17:48.806 --> 17:50.460
Conversation's over.

17:50.504 --> 17:52.767
Our business does not
concern you.

17:52.810 --> 17:55.204
I'm not arguing that, but
I'm leaving with her right now.

17:57.859 --> 18:00.514
I thought I told you
not to run into me again.

18:03.952 --> 18:06.781
You really don't know
who my father is, do you?

18:11.481 --> 18:14.354
[grunting]

18:14.397 --> 18:15.485
[grunts]

18:19.141 --> 18:21.491
[both grunting]

18:27.193 --> 18:28.672
[woman screams]

18:31.066 --> 18:32.502
[groans]

18:37.551 --> 18:39.335
[yells]

18:52.566 --> 18:54.742
Where did you learn to do that?

18:54.785 --> 18:55.960
It's not important right now.

18:56.004 --> 18:57.484
To me, it is.

18:57.527 --> 18:59.616
Self-defense class.

18:59.660 --> 19:02.010
Liar. The way
you fight,

19:02.053 --> 19:04.186
how you knew Willie's
nose wasn't broken

19:04.230 --> 19:05.535
just by
looking at it.

19:05.579 --> 19:07.015
Who are you?

19:07.058 --> 19:08.930
You-you can help
my mother and me.

19:08.973 --> 19:10.366
No, okay? No.

19:10.410 --> 19:12.194
I'm not your answer.
I'm sorry.

19:12.238 --> 19:13.761
With Arthur Novak.

19:13.804 --> 19:15.502
We'll go see him, and
you'll end this thing for us.

19:15.545 --> 19:17.243
Weare not doing anything.

19:17.286 --> 19:20.202
Delfina, what happened
back there-- it was a mistake.

19:20.246 --> 19:22.683
You got it? You and your mother
need to call the police

19:22.726 --> 19:24.511
and let the proper authorities
handle this.

19:24.554 --> 19:27.688
Of course. That's what we need
to do. Go to the police.

19:27.731 --> 19:29.211
Why didn't my mother
and I think of that?

19:29.255 --> 19:31.170
Dumb, dumb women.

19:31.213 --> 19:32.693
The Novaks hold the police
in their hands.

19:32.736 --> 19:34.216
I'm sorry to hear that.

19:34.260 --> 19:36.218
But I didn't leave
a bad situation back home

19:36.262 --> 19:38.394
to get caught up
in another one here.

19:38.438 --> 19:40.440
This isn't my job.

19:43.225 --> 19:45.271
What happened to you
in Los Angeles?

19:47.273 --> 19:48.839
You didn't seem the kind
of man to turn your back

19:48.883 --> 19:50.014
on people who need you.

19:50.058 --> 19:52.408
Now I do feel dumb.

19:52.452 --> 19:53.931
I'll walk home.

19:57.370 --> 19:59.328
Delfina?

20:02.462 --> 20:04.942
I'll see what I can do
to help, all right?

20:04.986 --> 20:07.249
Now, will you please
just get in?

20:07.293 --> 20:09.077
Please.

20:09.120 --> 20:11.122
[Spanish music playing]

20:22.133 --> 20:24.440
HONDO:
What happened
the day your husband died?

20:24.484 --> 20:26.399
Miguel and Gabriel went
to the canyon

20:26.442 --> 20:30.403
to drill for water
and set up a new well.

20:30.446 --> 20:32.405
How did the accident happen?

20:32.448 --> 20:33.754
We don't know
all the details.

20:33.797 --> 20:35.408
Drilling a well...

20:35.451 --> 20:37.888
My father had done it
many times before.

20:37.932 --> 20:39.412
It's always dangerous,
and that day...

20:39.455 --> 20:42.328
That day, something happened
with the equipment.

20:44.199 --> 20:46.767
Miguel was hit in the head
and died.

20:46.810 --> 20:48.551
Instantly.

20:48.595 --> 20:50.466
Was there an investigation?

20:50.510 --> 20:52.468
People came.

20:52.512 --> 20:54.731
We were told it was an accident.How long after

20:54.775 --> 20:57.604
Miguel died did Arthur Novak
make you an offer?

20:57.647 --> 20:59.736
One whole day.

20:59.780 --> 21:01.434
We hadn't even buried
my father before A.J. came

21:01.477 --> 21:03.479
with his father's money
like a vulture.

21:07.048 --> 21:09.877
Where exactly was
your father drilling?

21:28.243 --> 21:30.637
♪

21:39.298 --> 21:41.300
♪

21:43.519 --> 21:45.478
PALOMA:
Leo Ramirez, probably.

21:45.521 --> 21:48.002
He's the man around here
for drilling wells.

21:48.045 --> 21:50.831
Everyone uses him,
though I don't know why.

21:50.874 --> 21:53.007
He's a rip-off.

21:53.050 --> 21:55.836
If Leo sneezes on the job,
he'll charge you for the tissue.

21:55.879 --> 21:58.491
Do you know anything about
A.J. Novak's father, Arthur?

21:58.534 --> 22:01.668
Nothing... other than
he's a millionaire

22:01.711 --> 22:03.583
who owns properties
all over the world.

22:03.626 --> 22:06.368
He comes from Europe?Maybe.

22:06.412 --> 22:09.328
I heard Ireland
because of his accent.

22:09.371 --> 22:11.373
Then it was Hungary.

22:11.417 --> 22:13.854
Then there were rumors
about he was Russian mob.

22:13.897 --> 22:16.073
No one really knows.

22:16.117 --> 22:17.858
How long's he been here?

22:17.901 --> 22:20.208
A year, little more.

22:20.251 --> 22:21.862
He's built a hotel,

22:21.905 --> 22:24.473
converted a historical building
into a bar,

22:24.517 --> 22:26.562
bought up some ranches.

22:26.606 --> 22:28.869
A lot of people like the money
he brings in,

22:28.912 --> 22:33.395
but some have lost jobs,
and crime has gone up.

22:33.439 --> 22:35.615
Do you know this
Leo Ramirez well enough

22:35.658 --> 22:37.486
to give him a call and
have him stop by here?

22:37.530 --> 22:39.140
I'd like to ask him
a couple questions,

22:39.183 --> 22:40.794
if you could
translate for me.

22:40.837 --> 22:45.668
You need me to translate?
With your wonderful Spanish?

22:45.712 --> 22:48.367
I'll call him.Paloma, one last thing.

22:48.410 --> 22:50.891
What's the password
for the Internet here?

22:50.934 --> 22:54.242
You made me promise to never
tell you that, remember?

22:54.285 --> 22:56.418
You were getting away
from the world.

23:33.803 --> 23:35.414
Delfina.

23:41.376 --> 23:42.377
¿Pero mami?

23:49.428 --> 23:50.994
Gracias.

24:10.797 --> 24:12.799
[engine starts]

24:24.158 --> 24:27.335
[knocking]That must be Leo.

24:33.994 --> 24:35.212
Step outside, please.

24:37.606 --> 24:39.478
You want to tell me why?

24:39.521 --> 24:41.044
I warned you not
to be a hero.

24:41.088 --> 24:43.394
You sent three men to the
hospital, one with a broken leg.

24:43.438 --> 24:45.745
They threatened Delfina Reyes,
and then they attacked me.

24:45.788 --> 24:47.747
We have three victims
who say you were the aggressor.

24:49.923 --> 24:51.925
I have no choice.

24:56.799 --> 24:58.192
I have to do my job.

24:58.235 --> 24:59.410
Is that the lie
you tell yourself

24:59.454 --> 25:01.456
so you can sleep at night?

25:21.998 --> 25:23.478
[quietly]:
Vamos.

25:32.139 --> 25:33.923
♪

25:48.459 --> 25:49.852
This is Chief Barrera.

25:49.896 --> 25:51.071
When am I being released?

25:51.114 --> 25:52.855
Ustedes Americanos...

25:52.899 --> 25:56.076
[continues in Spanish]

25:56.119 --> 25:57.730
The chief says he has
no patience for outsiders

25:57.773 --> 25:59.601
coming to our peaceful town
causing mayhem.

25:59.645 --> 26:01.211
[speaking Spanish]

26:01.255 --> 26:02.909
We believe
in law and order here.

26:02.952 --> 26:05.999
Not so hot on the truth, though.

26:06.042 --> 26:08.001
[speaking Spanish]

26:08.044 --> 26:10.046
He wants you to know that
you are facing serious charges

26:10.090 --> 26:12.527
for attacking and
terrorizing our citizens.

26:12.571 --> 26:14.398
[speaking Spanish]Fortunately for you,

26:14.442 --> 26:16.531
Señor Novak is a generous man.

26:16.575 --> 26:18.098
[speaking Spanish]

26:18.141 --> 26:20.100
He might persuade his son
and his associates

26:20.143 --> 26:21.841
to drop their charges...He mightpersuade them?

26:21.884 --> 26:24.234
[speaking Spanish]Novak would like to meet you.

26:24.278 --> 26:26.280
You're to join him
for lunch at his hotel.

26:26.323 --> 26:27.977
And if I'd rather not?

26:28.021 --> 26:31.024
[speaking Spanish]

26:32.286 --> 26:34.854
Then you will be
booked and charged.

26:34.897 --> 26:36.899
It's your choice.

27:04.361 --> 27:05.972
You must be the man of the hour.

27:06.015 --> 27:07.495
And you must be
Arthur Novak.

27:07.538 --> 27:09.279
The cause of all the problems
around here.

27:09.323 --> 27:11.281
[laughs]
In negotiations,

27:11.325 --> 27:13.501
we call that "a non-starter."

27:13.544 --> 27:15.111
Is that what this is?

27:15.155 --> 27:17.026
A negotiation?I hope so.

27:17.070 --> 27:19.638
But first, you must
be thirsty, starving.

27:19.681 --> 27:21.683
Please, sit.

27:21.727 --> 27:25.295
The ceviche here--
you won't find better anywhere.

27:25.339 --> 27:27.820
They use this garlic chili oil.

27:27.863 --> 27:29.865
Fantastic.

27:33.260 --> 27:34.827
Mister...?

27:34.870 --> 27:37.003
Harrelson.Well, Mr. Harrelson,

27:37.046 --> 27:38.831
don't you know
that an invitation

27:38.874 --> 27:42.008
to eat and drink
is a show of affection here?

27:42.051 --> 27:44.010
I do.

27:44.053 --> 27:46.012
That's why I'm declining.

27:46.055 --> 27:49.624
You wanted to talk,
so... talk.

27:49.668 --> 27:52.366
No foreplay?
Just down and dirty.

27:52.409 --> 27:53.715
I understand.

27:53.759 --> 27:55.804
Shame, though.

27:57.719 --> 27:59.982
Look, I've been sweating
my ass off in jail

28:00.026 --> 28:02.028
on trumped-up charges, so...Trumped-up?

28:02.071 --> 28:03.551
My employee won't walk
for two months.

28:03.594 --> 28:05.248
I tried to leave
with Delfina peacefully.

28:05.292 --> 28:07.381
Your employee wanted that fight,
so that's what he got.

28:07.424 --> 28:09.209
But you already know that.

28:09.252 --> 28:11.037
I'll tell you what I don't know:
who you are.

28:11.080 --> 28:13.039
Just a guy staying

28:13.082 --> 28:15.563
at his friend's place in Mexico
enjoying the peace and quiet.

28:15.606 --> 28:17.608
At least I was
until I met your son.

28:17.652 --> 28:19.915
[laughs]
My son.

28:19.959 --> 28:23.440
Heart's in the right place,
but his temper...

28:23.484 --> 28:26.443
Like his no-good mother,
God rest her soul.

28:27.749 --> 28:29.185
What are you looking for
from me?

28:29.229 --> 28:31.144
Looking for?To walk away from all this?

28:31.187 --> 28:32.667
I don't want anything
from you.

28:32.711 --> 28:34.060
But when I see someone
harming an old man

28:34.103 --> 28:35.452
and threatening a young woman,

28:35.496 --> 28:37.019
I ain't about
to walk away from that.

28:37.063 --> 28:39.500
So, you're a man
with a savior complex.

28:39.543 --> 28:41.981
Must make life so stressful.

28:42.024 --> 28:44.635
I don't blame you for
running away from your home.

28:44.679 --> 28:46.855
And you, Arthur?

28:46.899 --> 28:48.552
Who are you exactly?

28:52.948 --> 28:56.517
I'm just a man
enjoying delicious food,

28:56.560 --> 28:58.824
good company

28:58.867 --> 29:01.348
and a spectacular view.Yeah?

29:02.392 --> 29:04.307
Well, from what I read,

29:04.351 --> 29:06.657
your home country of Ireland
doesn't want to let you back in,

29:06.701 --> 29:08.137
and Ukrainian and
Slovakian authorities

29:08.181 --> 29:09.704
would love to get
their hands on you.

29:09.748 --> 29:11.575
I'm guessing that's why
you ended up in Mexico.

29:12.751 --> 29:14.753
No extradition treaty.

29:17.886 --> 29:19.845
You've been a busy boy.

29:19.888 --> 29:22.108
Don't call me "boy."But you're a fool

29:22.151 --> 29:24.763
to judge a man
solely by his past.

29:24.806 --> 29:26.895
Lucky for you, I don't.

29:26.939 --> 29:29.637
Otherwise, you'd be sleeping
in that jail cell.

29:29.680 --> 29:31.117
You have a choice to make.

29:31.160 --> 29:33.902
Why don't you just leave
that family alone?

29:33.946 --> 29:36.122
That way I can go back to
what I was doing-- nothing.

29:36.165 --> 29:40.126
You haven't even heard my offer,
and already you're countering.

29:40.169 --> 29:43.825
Help me in the betterment
of this little town.

29:43.869 --> 29:46.306
With Delfina and Isabel Reyes?

29:46.349 --> 29:49.091
Sounds like they trust you.

29:49.135 --> 29:51.398
If anyone can convince them
to sell, it's you.

29:51.441 --> 29:52.834
My son and his friends
have tried,

29:52.878 --> 29:54.836
but so far, they've only failed.

29:54.880 --> 29:56.055
Maybe that's because
the Reyes women

29:56.098 --> 29:57.447
aren't interested in selling.

29:58.535 --> 30:01.190
If you want
the assault charges dropped,

30:01.234 --> 30:03.845
you will get them to sell.

30:03.889 --> 30:06.761
I'll even make it easier
for you.

30:06.805 --> 30:08.850
Tell them you convinced me

30:08.894 --> 30:11.853
to raise my offer by $100,000

30:11.897 --> 30:14.595
to end all this unpleasantness.

30:14.638 --> 30:16.640
Think you can do that?

30:24.866 --> 30:26.955
DELFINA:
$100,000 more?

30:28.391 --> 30:30.741
They can take that extra money
and shove it right up their...

30:30.785 --> 30:32.656
Okay, look, look,
I know this isn't ideal,

30:32.700 --> 30:34.093
but with all your workers
now gone...

30:34.136 --> 30:35.659
So you want us
to give up?

30:35.703 --> 30:37.966
Look, this is a problem
I can't fix for you.

30:38.010 --> 30:40.839
Maybe it's your
best option.Absolutely not.

30:47.323 --> 30:49.282
This is our home.

30:49.325 --> 30:50.718
Papi never would have sold.

30:54.765 --> 30:56.898
Daniel is right.No!

31:03.252 --> 31:05.428
Cheers.

31:09.041 --> 31:10.216
Mami...

31:10.259 --> 31:12.522
My body aches
all the time.

31:12.566 --> 31:15.699
My hands feel like sand
because they are so cracked.

31:15.743 --> 31:19.399
And I go to sleep only to spend
most of the night awake.

31:20.966 --> 31:23.055
I'm exhausted, mija.

31:24.230 --> 31:26.623
I don't have anything left in me
to give to this land.

31:31.977 --> 31:33.935
We will take his offer.

31:33.979 --> 31:36.024
I won't let you!

31:36.068 --> 31:38.897
It isn't your choice, mi amor.

31:40.420 --> 31:42.422
The property is in my name.

31:46.861 --> 31:49.603
[scoffs]

32:04.879 --> 32:07.012
Was that your idea of helping?

32:13.627 --> 32:16.282
I just spent the morning
in jail because I helped.

32:18.371 --> 32:20.503
I know.

32:20.547 --> 32:22.679
I'm sorry.

32:34.387 --> 32:37.129
Don't look at this
as you versus them.

32:37.172 --> 32:39.174
That's how they win.

32:44.614 --> 32:49.619
The first day I helped my father
on the farm, I only complained.

32:49.663 --> 32:53.841
So he pulled out 300 pesos,
told me he'd bury it.

32:53.884 --> 32:56.626
If I found it
by the end of the day,

32:56.670 --> 32:58.585
not only would I get to keep it,

32:58.628 --> 33:00.674
but I wouldn't have
to work again.

33:04.634 --> 33:06.636
I never found it.

33:11.990 --> 33:13.992
But then he rubbed soil
into my hands.

33:14.035 --> 33:17.125
It felt wet, coarse.

33:17.169 --> 33:20.302
He said, "Money is fleeting,

33:20.346 --> 33:24.872
but this land will never leave."

33:33.228 --> 33:35.187
Delfina,

33:35.230 --> 33:37.667
I think there's someone
we should talk to

33:37.711 --> 33:40.322
about the day your dad
and Gabriel were drilling.

33:40.366 --> 33:42.368
♪

34:00.255 --> 34:01.865
Hey, hey, señor.

34:01.909 --> 34:03.519
Ask him if he was

34:03.563 --> 34:05.217
at the drill site
the day your father died.

34:07.567 --> 34:08.916
Just ask him.

34:10.961 --> 34:13.616
[speaks Spanish]

34:18.578 --> 34:20.101
You tell him I want to know

34:20.145 --> 34:21.972
how Miguel's accident
really happened.

34:24.801 --> 34:27.195
I'm watching him now.
Meeting with Ramirez.

34:27.239 --> 34:28.631
Delfina is with him, too.

34:28.675 --> 34:30.111
Well, you can't say we didn't

34:30.155 --> 34:32.809
give them every opportunity
to just leave.

34:38.424 --> 34:40.513
You don't think my father's
death was an accident, do you?

34:42.558 --> 34:44.169
Neither do I.

34:44.212 --> 34:46.214
Would they go that far
to get what they want?

34:46.258 --> 34:48.782
To actually kill?We don't have
all the facts.

34:48.825 --> 34:50.131
Then we need to get them.

34:50.175 --> 34:51.828
"We"?

34:51.872 --> 34:55.919
Delfina, I'm not gonna be around
much longer.

34:55.963 --> 34:58.792
You're leaving? Now?No.

34:58.835 --> 35:00.489
I don't know when I'm leaving.

35:00.533 --> 35:02.317
But you're gonna have
to find a solution

35:02.361 --> 35:03.884
that doesn't involve me.

35:06.930 --> 35:10.108
[tires squealing]

35:10.151 --> 35:12.240
What's wrong?Hold on.

35:12.284 --> 35:13.372
Oh, my God.

35:41.400 --> 35:43.967
[gunfire]

35:44.011 --> 35:45.795
[tires squealing]

35:49.321 --> 35:51.323
♪

35:55.675 --> 35:58.243
Hold on to that seat belt tight!

35:58.286 --> 35:59.809
[tires screeching]

36:20.178 --> 36:21.135
[tires squealing]

36:21.179 --> 36:22.354
[yells]

36:26.836 --> 36:29.883
[people shouting]

36:32.668 --> 36:33.887
[horn blaring]

36:46.639 --> 36:48.293
You okay? Call your mother.Yeah.

36:48.336 --> 36:49.511
Have her meet you
at my place.

36:49.555 --> 36:50.773
You'll both be safer there

36:50.817 --> 36:52.471
until I get back.Where are you going?

37:00.566 --> 37:02.220
Thanks for meeting me.

37:02.263 --> 37:04.309
Well, I'm off duty, but I only
have a few minutes for this.

37:04.352 --> 37:05.875
Nobody's following you.How do you know?

37:05.919 --> 37:07.877
Because you're bottom
of the food chain.

37:07.921 --> 37:10.619
Too low to be considered a
threat. That's a good thing.

37:10.663 --> 37:13.231
That spider web that you call
a department? Your boss?

37:13.274 --> 37:15.276
You're not mixed up
with them yet.

37:15.320 --> 37:17.104
That's why you
can help me.

37:17.147 --> 37:18.801
I don't think Miguel Reyes's
death was an accident.

37:18.845 --> 37:20.238
I think he was killed.

37:20.281 --> 37:22.588
Killed? By who?

37:22.631 --> 37:23.937
The Novak associate

37:23.980 --> 37:25.155
who's a former employee
of the Reyes farm.

37:25.199 --> 37:26.679
Gabriel?I think he cut a deal

37:26.722 --> 37:28.028
with Arthur and A.J.

37:28.071 --> 37:30.073
to profit from the sale
of the Reyes farm.

37:30.117 --> 37:31.466
Now, if we took that
to your chief,

37:31.510 --> 37:33.686
would he do a proper
investigation?

37:33.729 --> 37:35.078
Just how corrupt
is Barrera?

37:35.122 --> 37:36.297
Well, he sometimes looks
the other way, but...

37:36.341 --> 37:38.168
Yeah, I know guys like that.No.

37:38.212 --> 37:40.606
If we had proof,
if we had physical evidence

37:40.649 --> 37:42.172
that Miguel Reyes
was murdered,

37:42.216 --> 37:44.305
there's no way Chief Barrera
could turn his back.

37:44.349 --> 37:46.655
Do you have proof?Right now, it's just a theory.

37:46.699 --> 37:48.614
A theor...

37:48.657 --> 37:50.572
[scoffs]
So your word against theirs?

37:52.487 --> 37:54.315
My word against theirs.

37:54.359 --> 37:56.361
Where have I heard that before?

37:57.362 --> 38:00.060
This job you signed up for--

38:00.103 --> 38:02.149
working for a man who
looks the other way?

38:02.192 --> 38:04.194
Forcing you to look
the other way?

38:04.238 --> 38:06.980
Compromising yourself
more and more every day?

38:07.023 --> 38:09.112
Does that really sit
right with you?

38:13.247 --> 38:16.206
If you can get me proof,

38:16.250 --> 38:18.296
I promise to do what I can.

38:25.390 --> 38:27.870
HONDO:
Go ahead.

38:27.914 --> 38:29.132
Try and cut into it.

38:29.176 --> 38:30.699
I'll give you 100 large
if you can.

38:36.401 --> 38:39.012
When I found out Miguel Reyes
was drilling for water

38:39.055 --> 38:41.014
and only hit stone, I wondered

38:41.057 --> 38:42.407
if it might have been
something else.

38:42.450 --> 38:44.278
Maybe something
more valuable.

38:44.322 --> 38:46.585
You knew there was silver
running under that farm.

38:46.628 --> 38:49.588
And?This whole time,
you've been siccing your dogs

38:49.631 --> 38:51.546
on those Reyes women,
trying to force them to sell

38:51.590 --> 38:53.374
for way less
than its real value.

38:53.418 --> 38:55.594
Those women being
ignorant of the value

38:55.637 --> 38:58.727
of their own property
is not my responsibility.

38:58.771 --> 39:00.381
And the husband, Miguel--

39:00.425 --> 39:02.035
he was quite dim.

39:02.078 --> 39:04.080
I've always taught my son

39:04.124 --> 39:06.692
that there's nothing
more useless

39:06.735 --> 39:09.738
than a stubborn, dumb old man,

39:09.782 --> 39:12.437
and that couldn't be more true
of Miguel.

39:13.960 --> 39:16.919
Tomorrow, you're gonna take
a drive out to the Reyes farm,

39:16.963 --> 39:18.921
and you're gonna meet
with Isabel and Delfina,

39:18.965 --> 39:21.359
and you're gonna offer them
the actual fair price,

39:21.402 --> 39:23.012
the price that they deserve.

39:26.799 --> 39:29.062
The price they deserve.

39:33.501 --> 39:38.506
Deserve for people like Isabel
and Delfina is always based

39:38.550 --> 39:40.813
on what people like
me think of them.

39:42.380 --> 39:45.165
My fair price now is one peso.

39:45.208 --> 39:47.385
One peso?

39:47.428 --> 39:51.737
Any fair offer is based solely
on what your power merits,

39:51.780 --> 39:57.612
and my power merits that "no"
is never a word I have to hear.

39:57.656 --> 40:00.789
Sadly, right now,
Isabel's power?

40:01.790 --> 40:03.836
It merits one peso.

40:06.839 --> 40:09.537
Isabel already said "no"
to your previous offer.

40:09.581 --> 40:11.147
Why in the hell would
she ever consider

40:11.191 --> 40:12.758
selling to you for...?

40:14.063 --> 40:16.022
Delfina.

40:16.065 --> 40:17.589
You son of a bitch.

40:22.071 --> 40:24.073
[phone ringing]

40:25.292 --> 40:26.467
Come on!

40:26.511 --> 40:28.077
[phone continues ringing]

40:28.121 --> 40:30.079
[recorded]: This is Anthony.
Sorry I missed your call.

40:30.123 --> 40:31.733
Please leave your name
and number.

40:31.777 --> 40:33.648
[beeps]

40:33.692 --> 40:36.216
HONDO: Delfina, pick up
the phone. It's Daniel.

40:36.259 --> 40:38.436
[muffled gasping]

40:44.093 --> 40:46.574
Delfina?! Delfina!

40:48.446 --> 40:51.231
Delfina? Delfin...

40:55.931 --> 40:58.804
I was in the stables,
and I heard screaming.

40:58.847 --> 41:01.284
By the time I ran in,
I heard a car drive off.

41:01.328 --> 41:03.765
She arrived just
after I did.

41:03.809 --> 41:07.247
What are they gonna do
to my girl? [gasps]

41:08.553 --> 41:10.468
CHARRO:
I can't believe

41:10.511 --> 41:13.383
they would take her
just like that. Are you sure?

41:13.427 --> 41:16.212
I understand.Charro, this is your chance

41:16.256 --> 41:18.040
to do the job you thought
you signed up for.

41:18.084 --> 41:20.216
Now, we can't bring
fists to a gunfight.

41:20.260 --> 41:22.697
Do you know where
we can weapon up?

41:22.741 --> 41:24.743
Follow me.

41:30.444 --> 41:31.793
We don't get
much shooting practice,

41:31.837 --> 41:33.708
so I had to teach myself.

41:33.752 --> 41:38.496
And... being police here,
it can be a dangerous job.

41:38.539 --> 41:41.542
I have to ask, Daniel.
Yes, we have guns.

41:41.586 --> 41:43.631
But how can we possibly
take on Arthur's private army?

41:43.675 --> 41:46.242
It's just us two
